<div class='box2_7 floatl m brdr'>
 <h1>Events</h1>
    <ul>
      <li><a href="http://atc-2001.tripod.com/">Asian Test Championship</a> - Includes   schedule, squads, pictures, scorecards, and records. </li>
      <li><a href="http://www.chiangmaisixes.com/">Chiang Mai Cricket Sixes in   Thailand</a> - An annual event run in Northern Thailand just before Easter each   year for club cricketers with invited Test stars playing in a friendly   competition. </li>
      <li><a href="http://www.hindustantimes.com/news/specials/natwest/home.shtml">NatWest Triangular Series </a> - Information from Hindustan Times offering schedules, squads, results, figures and grounds. </li>
      <li><a href="http://www.sportsecuritymanagement.com/">Sport Security   Management</a> - Sport security management ensures that major sports events   including the ICC Cricket World Cup are safe and incident free. Includes   information, a profile, training, contacts, and a chat room. </li>
      <li><a href="http://www.abcofcricket.com/Article_Library/news280804/news280804.htm">Videocon Cup</a> -   Live updates of the tri-nation challenge between India, Australia and Pakistan. </li>
      <li></li>
      </ul>
        <h2>The Ashes</h2>
        <ul>
      <li><a href="http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport2/hi/cricket/england/default.stm">BBC   Sport - Cricket: Ashes 2005</a> - Highlights and features of England's win,   including audio and video. </li>
      <li><a href="http://www.thebigproject.co.uk/ashes/index.htm">The Big Project -   Ashes Cricket Tour 2005</a> - Australia vs England match schedules plus   directory of news and media coverage, competition history, cricket portals and   organisations. Also links to Australian culture and travel information. </li>
      <li><a href="http://sport.guardian.co.uk/ashes2005/0,15993,1476227,00.html">Guardian   Unlimited Sport - Cricket: The Ashes 2005</a> - Complete over-by-over coverage   plus analysis and commentary of England's victory over Australia. </li>
      <li><a href="http://www.334notout.com/">334notout's Ashes 1877 - 2003</a> -   History, records, player profiles, news and commentary, match reports,   statistics and scorecards from both the Australian and English perspective. </li>
      <li></li>
      </ul>
 <h2>Indian Premier</h2>
           <ul>
          <li><a href="http://www.iplt20.com/">Indian Premier League</a>    - Official   site provides news, scorecards, videos and pictures. Free live streaming is   provided during the matches. </li>
          <li><a href="http://www.chennaisuperkings.com">Chennai Super Kings</a> -   Official website featuring latest news, statistics, player profiles and a   multimedia section. Facilitates online ticket booking. </li>
          <li><a href="http://www.cricinfo.com/ipl2009/content/series/374163.html">Cricinfo -   Indian Premier League</a> - News and information about the Indian Premier League   with live IPL scores, fixtures, results and features throughout the cricket   tournament. </li>
          <li><a href="http://www.deccanchargers.com/">Deccan Chargers</a> - Official   website for the team with current news, schedules and a fan forum. Also hosts   contests, picture gallery and videos. </li>
          <li><a href="http://www.delhidaredevils.com/">Delhi Daredevils</a> - Features   player profiles, downloads, ticket booking and a look into the official ground.   Also includes a blog and a fan forum. </li>
          <li><a href="http://fakeiplplayer.blogspot.com/">Fake IPL Player</a> - Humorous   blog purporting to be from an insider within the Kolkata Knight Riders' camp,   providing inside gossip about the team. </li>
          <li><a href="http://chennaisuperkings.blogspot.com">Fan Site of Chennai Super   Kings</a> - Blog providing news and information about the team. </li>
          <li><a href="http://www.iplcricketlive.com/">IPL Cricket Live</a> - Offers news   stories and updates of the league and some videos. </li>
          <li><a href="http://www.premierleaguenews.in">IPL News</a> - Provides news, live   score card, series schedule, and team information. </li>
          <li><a href="http://www.kkr.in/">Kolkata Knight Riders</a> - Find latest news ,   trivia, downloads and team details. Also enjoy watching Hooglee cartoons,   cheerleader videos and reading the blog. </li>
          <li><a href="http://www.rajasthanroyals.com">Rajasthan Royals</a> - Official   website , offering news, pictures, videos, mobile content and a online store.   Also maintains a tour diary and match wise statistics. </li>
          <li><a href="http://www.royalchallengers.com">Royal Challengers Bangalore</a> -   Official site for the team providing latest news, team details, videos and   downloads. Allows fans to create personalized email ids. </li>
          <li><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Indian_Premier_League">Wikipedia -   Indian Premier League</a> - Hyperlinked encyclopedia article about the DLF   League including franchises, players and controversies.</li>
          <li></li>
          </ul>
            <h2>World Cup</h2>
            <ul>
              <li><a href="http://www.cricinfo.com/db/ARCHIVE/WORLD_CUPS/">CricInfo - The   World Cup Archive</a> - Offers a brief history of the World Cup plus coverage of   individual tournaments including live audio coverage plus bulletins, Wisden   Verdicts, expert panel commentary and weekly video program. </li>
              <li><a href="http://cricket.com.au/default.aspx?s=worldcup2007">Cricket   Australia: ICC Cricket World Cup 2007</a> - News and information from the   official site of the Australian team. </li>
              <li><a href="http://sport.guardian.co.uk/cricketworldcup2003/">Guardian   Unlimited: Cricket World Cup 2003</a> - Full coverage includes all over-by-over   reports, highlighted by Scott Murray's incisive coverage of March 14, along with   news, history, and player profiles. </li>
              <li><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cricket_World_Cup">Wikipedia - Cricket   World Cup</a> - Hyperlinked encyclopedia article provides basic information and   a brief history of the World Cup. </li>
              <li><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2007_Cricket_World_Cup">Wikipedia:   2007 Cricket World Cup</a> - Extensive encyclopedia article with teams, rules,   fixtures, and scores.</li>
            </ul>
</div>
<div class='box2_7 floatl m brdr'>
 <h1>Cricket Organizations</h1>
    <ul>
      <li><a href="http://www.icc-cricket.com/">International Cricket Council</a><br />
        The   governing body for cricket throughout the world. </li>
      <li><a href="http://www.lords.org/">Lord's</a><br />
        ICC and ECB home of cricket at Marylebone Cricket Club.  Includes news, virtal tour of the Long Room, history and official laws of cricket, online shopping and ticket sales.
      </li>
      <li><a href="http://www.ecb.co.uk/">English Cricket Board (ECB)</a><br />
        The   official home of the ECB on the internet. The most comprehensive and detailed   coverage of the England cricket team and all cricket in England and Wales. </li>
      <li><a href="http://www.nzcricket.co.nz/">New Zealand Cricket</a><br />
        Official   site of New Zealand cricket, including news, tickets, columns, statistics, and   more. </li>
      <li><a href="http://www.cricket.com.au/">Cricket Australia</a><br />
        News and   information site from the governing body of cricket in Australia. </li>
      <li><a href="http://www.auscricket.com.au/">Australian Cricketers   Association</a><br />
        The representative voice of first class cricketers in   Australia. </li>
      <li><a href="http://www.cricketsa.com.au/">South Australian Cricket   Association</a><br />
        Official site for the picturesque cricket ground and home to   the West End Redbacks in South Australia. Includes a history of the grounds, a   virtual tour, and a calendar of events. </li>
      <li><a href="http://www.aicf.com.au/">Australian Indoor Cricket   Federation</a><br />
        Information about the sport, calendar of events, results, and   photos. </li>
      <li><a href="http://www.waca.com.au/">Western Australian Cricket Association   (WACA)</a><br />
        Official site for the cricket grounds that serve as home to the   Retravision Warriors. Includes latest news, hospitality information, and   upcoming events. </li>
      <li><a href="http://www.cricket.co.za/">Cricket South Africa</a><br />
        Official   site of the United Cricket Board of South Africa. Features news, player   profiles, domestic competitions, international fixtures, and statistics. </li>
      <li><a href="http://www.canadiancricket.org/">Canadian Cricket Association   (CCA)</a><br />
        Official site of the cricket control authority in Canada. Site   features player profiles, cricket stats, tour information, and domestic   tournament details. </li>
      <li><a href="http://www.usaca.org/">United States of America Cricket   Association</a><br />
        The United States of America Cricket Association (USACA) is   the governing body for cricket in the United States of America. </li>
      <li><a href="http://www.swisscricket.ch/">Swiss Cricket   Association</a><br />
        The Swiss Cricket Association has been recognized by the   Swiss Olympic Committee as the sole governing body for cricket in the country. </li>
      <li><a href="http://www.swissfocus.org/">Swiss Federation of Cricket Umpires and   Scorers</a><br />
        Promoting and developing cricket umpiring and scoring in   Switzerland. </li>
      <li><a href="http://www.hkca.cricket.org/">Hong Kong Cricket   Association</a><br />
        Governing body for cricket in Hong Kong. </li>
      <li><a href="http://www.bermudacricketboard.com/">Bermuda Cricket   Board</a><br />
        Official site of the cricket control body in Bermuda. Site features   current squad, domestic league news, and latest match results. </li>
    </ul>
</div>

